│ stop({"edit_points": [[3231, 3234, "llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1. Understanding the Issue:\n\nThe issue is that the transformation from       │
│ `select i1 %c1, i1 %c2, i1 false` to `and i1 %c1, %c2` is not poison-safe when dealing with `icmp samesign` instructions. The problem occurs because `%c2` (icmp samesign eq i32 %In, 1)  │
│ can be poison for certain inputs like %In = -2147483648 (0x80000000), while `%c1` (icmp samesign sgt i32 %In, -1) evaluates to false for the same input.\n\nIn the original code, when    │
│ %c1 is false, the select returns false regardless of whether %c2 is poison. However, in the transformed code (and i1 %c1, %c2), both operands are evaluated, and if %c2 is poison, the    │
