│ for `icmp samesign` instructions, `TrueVal` can be poison regardless of `CondVal`'s value.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n\nThe fix is to add an additional check to ensure that          │
│ `TrueVal` cannot be poison when `CondVal` is false. However, since this is complex to analyze precisely, a simpler and safer approach is to avoid this transformation when either operand │
